section.section:
"Participating agencies and programs" includes:
Public prekindergarten and kindergarten programs;
Head Start programs;
Family literacy programs and services;
Local infants and toddlers programs;
Child care centers and family child care homes;
Family support centers;
Healthy family sites;
Parent involvement programs;
Early childhood programs affiliated with institutions of higher education; and
Other home visiting, community health, family support services, and child care resource and referral agencies.

Funds that are allocated to the Program in the State budget may be used:
To cover the costs incurred by the Department in implementing and administering the Program;
For Judy Center Grants, as provided under subsection (d) of this section;
For Early Child Care and Education Enhancement Grants, as provided under subsection (e) of this section; and
To fund the statewide implementation of the Department's Early Childhood Assessment System, as provided under subsection (f) of this section.
